## Setup

{% if full_stack %}
```bash
# Backend
cd api
uv sync --all-extras
uv run pre-commit install
cd ..

# Frontend
pnpm install
```
{% else %}
```bash
uv sync --all-extras
uv run pre-commit install
```
{% endif %}

Then enable release-please: go to **Settings > Actions > General > Workflow permissions** and check **Allow GitHub Actions to create and approve pull requests**.
{% if enable_github_pm %}

### Project Management Setup

After pushing to GitHub, run the bootstrap script to set up your Project board, labels, and custom fields:

```bash
./scripts/bootstrap-pm.sh
```

See [`docs/project-management.md`](docs/project-management.md) for how to work with issues, the label system, and the idea capture workflow.
{% endif %}

## Development

{% if full_stack %}
| Task | Command |
|---|---|
| Dev (both) | `npx nx run-many -t serve` |
| API only | `npx nx run api:serve` |
| UI only | `npx nx run ui:serve` |
| API test | `cd api && uv run pytest --tb=short` |
| API lint | `cd api && uv run ruff check src/ tests/` |
| API format | `cd api && uv run ruff format src/ tests/` |
| API type check | `cd api && uv run ty check src/ tests/` |
| UI type check | `cd ui && npx vue-tsc --noEmit` |
| UI build | `cd ui && npx vite build` |
{% else %}
| Task | Command |
|---|---|
| Test | `uv run pytest --tb=short` |
| Lint | `uv run ruff check src/ tests/` |
| Format | `uv run ruff format src/ tests/` |
| Type check | `uv run ty check src/ tests/` |
{% endif %}

